{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/blog/carbon-a-powerful-successor-of-c","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"excerpt":"Carbon programming language  The successor to C++ Google has recently announced a new programming language called Carbon that took the…","html":"<h1 id=\"Carbon-programming-language\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#Carbon-programming-language\" aria-label=\"Carbon programming language permalink\" class=\"gatsby-remark-autolink before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Carbon programming language</h1>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/4123f61e2246452500af5f385164d41e/e5166/carbon.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 52.02702702702703%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"promiseallsvg\"\n        title=\"promiseallsvg\"\n        src=\"/static/4123f61e2246452500af5f385164d41e/1c72d/carbon.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/4123f61e2246452500af5f385164d41e/a80bd/carbon.jpg 148w,\n/static/4123f61e2246452500af5f385164d41e/1c91a/carbon.jpg 295w,\n/static/4123f61e2246452500af5f385164d41e/1c72d/carbon.jpg 590w,\n/static/4123f61e2246452500af5f385164d41e/a8a14/carbon.jpg 885w,\n/static/4123f61e2246452500af5f385164d41e/fbd2c/carbon.jpg 1180w,\n/static/4123f61e2246452500af5f385164d41e/e5166/carbon.jpg 1200w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">promiseallsvg</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<h4 id=\"The-successor-to-C\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#The-successor-to-C\" aria-label=\"The successor to C permalink\" class=\"gatsby-remark-autolink before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>The successor to C++</h4>\n<p>Google has recently announced a new programming language called Carbon that took the attention due to the title \"A powerful successor of C++\". Most of the programmers have even a small experience with programming languages such as go, rust, kotlin, or typescript and you must have felt the significant boundaries and limitations with low-level operations, performance issues, and also migration from C++. The technical debt of C++ difficulties of its evolution process prevents us to inherit the legacy of C and C++. That is why Google made an initiation to start with a new language from scratch and based on a modern generic system to address these problems with simpler syntax and a modular code organization. For now, Carbon programming language is in the experiment stage, It is open-source and can be downloaded from the official GitHub repository.</p>\n<p>As we said Carbon is a successor of C++ fundamentally and it has been designed around interoperability with C++ and as a large-scale migration from the existing C++ codebase. Based on this definition such a language should address the following issues fundamentally</p>\n<ul>\n<li>matching performance</li>\n<li>Bidirectional interoperability with C++</li>\n<li>an easy and clear learning curve for C+= developers</li>\n<li>Support for existing software design and architectures</li>\n<li>Scalable migration with a source-to-source translation for C++ code</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If such a language can meet the essentials above then we can migrate the existing C++ developers community, investments, and codebases. Following programming languages respected the aforementioned essentials and have the same design model.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Java → Kotlin</li>\n<li>javascript → Typescript</li>\n<li>C++ → Carbon</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Carbon helloworld</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-text line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-text\">package main;\n\nfun main()->32{\n    Print(\"Hello Carbon\");\n}</code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n<h3 id=\"Carbon-and-C-example\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#Carbon-and-C-example\" aria-label=\"Carbon and C example permalink\" class=\"gatsby-remark-autolink before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Carbon and C++ example</h3>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"cpp\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-cpp line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-cpp\"><span class=\"token macro property\"><span class=\"token directive-hash\">#</span><span class=\"token directive keyword\">include</span> <span class=\"token string\">&lt;iostream></span></span>\n<span class=\"token macro property\"><span class=\"token directive-hash\">#</span><span class=\"token directive keyword\">include</span> <span class=\"token string\">&lt;vector></span></span>\n<span class=\"token macro property\"><span class=\"token directive-hash\">#</span><span class=\"token directive keyword\">include</span><span class=\"token string\">&lt;algorithm></span></span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">void</span> <span class=\"token function\">DoubleElement</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token keyword\">int</span> number<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    number<span class=\"token operator\">=</span>number <span class=\"token operator\">*</span> <span class=\"token number\">2</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    std<span class=\"token double-colon punctuation\">::</span>cout<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;&lt;</span>number<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">int</span> <span class=\"token function\">main</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    std<span class=\"token double-colon punctuation\">::</span>vector<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token keyword\">int</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span> numbers<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    numbers<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">push_back</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">15</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    numbers<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">push_back</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">16</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"token function\">for_each</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>numbers<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">begin</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> numbers<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">end</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> DoubleElement<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    \n<span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"token number\">0</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-text line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-text\">// Carbon\npackage main;\nimport Console;\n\nfn doubleElement(number: i32){\n    number+=number;\n    Console.Print(number);\n}\n\nfn Main() -> i32{\n    var numbers:[i32;];\n    numbers[0]=15;\n    numbers[1]=16;\n    for (var number: i32 in numbers){\n    doubleElement(number);\n    }\n\n}</code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n<h3 id=\"Try-carbon-with-Carbon-explorer\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#Try-carbon-with-Carbon-explorer\" aria-label=\"Try carbon with Carbon explorer permalink\" class=\"gatsby-remark-autolink before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Try carbon with Carbon explorer</h3>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-bash line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token comment\"># Install bazelisk using Homebrew.</span>\n$ brew <span class=\"token function\">install</span> bazelisk\n\n<span class=\"token comment\"># Install Clang/LLVM using Homebrew.</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\"># Many Clang/LLVM releases aren't built with options we rely on.</span>\n$ brew <span class=\"token function\">install</span> llvm\n$ <span class=\"token builtin class-name\">export</span> <span class=\"token assign-left variable\"><span class=\"token environment constant\">PATH</span></span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"<span class=\"token variable\"><span class=\"token variable\">$(</span>brew --prefix llvm<span class=\"token variable\">)</span></span>/bin:<span class=\"token variable\">${<span class=\"token environment constant\">PATH</span>}</span>\"</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\"># Download Carbon's code.</span>\n$ <span class=\"token function\">git</span> clone https://github.com/carbon-language/carbon-lang\n$ <span class=\"token builtin class-name\">cd</span> carbon-lang\n\n<span class=\"token comment\"># Build and run the explorer.</span>\n$ bazel run //explorer -- ./explorer/testdata/print/format_only.carbon</code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n<h3 id=\"Noticable-Carbon-features\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#Noticable-Carbon-features\" aria-label=\"Noticable Carbon features permalink\" class=\"gatsby-remark-autolink before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Noticable Carbon features</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Introducer keywords and a simple grammar</li>\n<li>Function input parameters are readonly values</li>\n<li>Pointers provide indirect access &#x26; mutation</li>\n<li>Use expressions to name types</li>\n<li>The package is the root namespace</li>\n<li>Import APIs through their package name</li>\n<li>Explicit object parameter declares a method</li>\n<li>Single inheritance; classes are final by default</li>\n<li>Powerful, definition-checked generics</li>\n<li>Types explicitly implement interfaces</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Although based on the definition and the approach of Carbon it seems to be a very powerful and Performance-critical language and a successor of C++, it is in the first stage and needs more contribution and work. <a href=\"%5Bcarbon-lang/CONTRIBUTING.md%20at%20trunk%20%C2%B7%20carbon-language/carbon-lang%20%C2%B7%20GitHub%5D(https://github.com/carbon-language/carbon-lang/blob/trunk/CONTRIBUTING.md)\">Here</a> you can find out how you can contribute.</p>","timeToRead":3,"id":"c6cc4b90-f297-5db3-a310-4a282f5f97ec","frontmatter":{"date":"July 23, 2022","title":"Carbon a powerful successor of C++"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/blog/carbon-a-powerful-successor-of-c"}},"staticQueryHashes":["1033876704","3435786681","550521386"]}